{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863601662,"sessionID":"ses_286483c20ffeCB3c9r8P9Xxksn","part":{"id":"prt_d79b815d400163j4cV658s4RyK","messageID":"msg_d79b805e2001T21p1zrJ0GXd75","sessionID":"ses_286483c20ffeCB3c9r8P9Xxksn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_8c5324f41b6a451aa978aa0f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","limit":150,"offset":1150},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1150:   enabled: true\n1151:   replicas: 2\n1152:   \n1153: picod:\n1154:   enabled: true  # Deployed as sidecar in sandbox pods\n1155: \n1156: ---\n1157: \n1158: # AR-022 — CLI Publish Command\n1159: \n1160: - **AR ID**: AR-022\n1161: - **Module**: cmd/cli\n1162: - **Language**: Python\n1163: - **Size**: L\n1164: \n1165: ---\n1166: \n1167: ## 9. CLI Toolkit Specification\n1168: \n1169: ### Purpose\n1170: \n1171: Command-line tool (`kubectl-agentcube`) for packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and checking status of AI agents against AgentCube or standard Kubernetes.\n1172: \n1173: ### Requirements\n1174: \n1175: #### Requirement: Global CLI options\n1176: The system SHALL expose a Typer application named `agentcube` with global options on the root callback.\n1177: \n1178: ##### Scenario: Version display\n1179: - **GIVEN** the CLI is installed and importable\n1180: - **WHEN** the user passes `--version` (eager option, `Optional[bool]`, default `None`)\n1181: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `AgentCube CLI (kubectl agentcube) version: {__version__}` (Rich markup) and exit without running a subcommand (`typer.Exit()`), where `__version__` is `0.1.0` from `agentcube.__init__`\n1182: \n1183: ##### Scenario: Global verbose logging\n1184: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` / `-v` (`bool`, default `False`) on the root callback\n1185: - **WHEN** the callback runs\n1186: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)`\n1187: \n1188: #### Requirement: `pack` command\n1189: The system SHALL provide `pack` to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a `Dockerfile`, and report paths.\n1190: \n1191: ##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n1192: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack`\n1193: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n1194: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`); `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, `Optional[str]`); `language` = `None` (`--language`); `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`); `port` = `None` (`--port`, `Optional[int]`); `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`); `description` = `None` (`--description`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, command-local)\n1195: \n1196: ##### Scenario: Successful pack\n1197: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path\n1198: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n1199: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success with `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path` (reported as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`), using a Rich `Progress` spinner during work\n1200: \n1201: ##### Scenario: Pack failure handling\n1202: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises\n1203: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n1204: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red, print a full traceback, and exit with code `1`\n1205: \n1206: #### Requirement: `build` command\n1207: The system SHALL build a container image from a packaged workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default in metadata), with optional proxy and tag derived from metadata version.\n1208: \n1209: ##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n1210: - **GIVEN** the user runs `build`\n1211: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n1212: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`); `proxy` = `None` (`-p` / `--proxy`); `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`); `output` = `None` (`--output`); `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`)\n1213: \n1214: ##### Scenario: Local Docker build prerequisites\n1215: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n1216: - **WHEN** Docker is unavailable\n1217: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")` surfaced via CLI error handling\n1218: \n1219: ##### Scenario: Version increment on build\n1220: - **GIVEN** a successful local build path\n1221: - **WHEN** `BuildRuntime.build` runs\n1222: - **THEN** the system SHALL increment `metadata.version` (patch bump for `X.Y.Z`, or append `.1` / fallback `{version}-1`) before build and revert the version in metadata if build fails\n1223: \n1224: #### Requirement: `publish` command\n1225: The system SHALL publish/deploy using provider `agentcube` (AgentRuntime CR) or `k8s` (Deployment + NodePort Service), preparing the image via Docker push or explicit image URL as implemented in `PublishRuntime`.\n1226: \n1227: ##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n1228: - **GIVEN** the user runs `publish`\n1229: - **THEN** defaults SHALL include: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `version` = `None` (`--version`); `image_url` = `None` (`--image-url`); `image_username` = `None` (`--image-username`); `image_password` = `None` (`--image-password`); `description` = `None`; `region` = `None` (`--region`); `cloud_provider` = `None`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"` (`--provider`); `node_port` = `None` (`--node-port`, `Optional[int]`); `replicas` = `None` (`--replicas`); `namespace` = `None` (`--namespace`); `verbose` = `False`\n1230: \n1231: ##### Scenario: AgentCube provider prerequisites\n1232: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `agentcube`\n1233: - **WHEN** metadata lacks `router_url` or `workload_manager_url`\n1234: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message requiring both fields in `agent_metadata.yaml`\n1235: \n1236: ##### Scenario: Standard Kubernetes publish flow\n1237: - **GIVEN** `provider` is `k8s` and Kubernetes client initializes\n1238: - **WHEN** publish proceeds\n1239: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `KubernetesProvider.deploy_agent`, then `wait_for_deployment_ready(..., timeout=120)`, updating metadata with deployment info; on readiness failure it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` after recording error in metadata\n1240: \n1241: #### Requirement: `invoke` command\n1242: The system SHALL POST JSON to the published agent endpoint, parse `--payload` as JSON, merge optional `--header` entries, and for AgentRuntime CR deployments rewrite the URL to `{base}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/` when `k8s_deployment.type == \"AgentRuntime\"`.\n1243: \n1244: ##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n1245: - **GIVEN** the user runs `invoke`\n1246: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `payload` = `\"{}\"` (`--payload`, `str`); `header_list` = `None` (`--header`, repeatable `List[str]`); `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n1247: \n1248: ##### Scenario: Invalid payload\n1249: - **GIVEN** `payload` is not valid JSON\n1250: - **WHEN** the command parses it\n1251: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print invalid JSON in red and exit with code `1` (before `_handle_error`)\n1252: \n1253: ##### Scenario: Invalid header format\n1254: - **GIVEN** a header string without a single `:` separator\n1255: - **WHEN** headers are parsed\n1256: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print expected `key:value` format and exit with code `1`\n1257: \n1258: ##### Scenario: Session header on invoke\n1259: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `session_id`\n1260: - **WHEN** `InvokeRuntime.invoke` runs\n1261: - **THEN** the HTTP client SHALL add header `X-Agentcube-Session-Id` (same spelling as response handling) to the request\n1262: \n1263: #### Requirement: `status` command\n1264: The system SHALL load workspace metadata and display agent status in a Rich `Table`, exiting with code `1` when status is `not_published` or `error`.\n1265: \n1266: ##### Scenario: Options and defaults\n1267: - **GIVEN** the user runs `status`\n1268: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be: `workspace` = `\".\"`; `provider` = `\"agentcube\"`; `verbose` = `False`\n1269: \n1270: ##### Scenario: Not published\n1271: - **GIVEN** metadata has no `agent_id`\n1272: - **WHEN** `get_status` returns `status == \"not_published\"`\n1273: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print guidance to publish first and exit with code `1`\n1274: \n1275: #### Requirement: Workspace validation (pack path)\n1276: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists and is a directory; for Python, require at least one `*.py` file; for Java, require `pom.xml`.\n1277: \n1278: ##### Scenario: Missing workspace\n1279: - **GIVEN** `workspace_path` does not exist\n1280: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n1281: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message that the directory does not exist\n1282: \n1283: ##### Scenario: Python workspace without Python files\n1284: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n1285: - **WHEN** no `*.py` exists in the workspace root\n1286: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n1287: \n1288: #### Requirement: Metadata file format\n1289: The system SHALL persist agent configuration as YAML. The primary filename SHALL be `agent_metadata.yaml`; loading SHALL fall back to `agent.yaml` then `metadata.yaml` if the primary file is missing.\n1290: \n1291: ##### Scenario: Save location\n1292: - **GIVEN** metadata is saved\n1293: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n1294: - **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, excluding `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n1295: \n1296: ##### Scenario: Schema validation\n1297: - **GIVEN** YAML is loaded\n1298: - **WHEN** fields violate `AgentMetadata` validators\n1299: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL reject unsupported `language` / `build_mode` or invalid `port` range\n\n(Showing lines 1150-1299 of 2062. Use offset=1300 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  enabled: true\n  replicas: 2\n  \npicod:\n  enabled: true  # Deployed as sidecar in sandbox pods\n\n---\n\n# AR-022 — CLI Publish Command\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-022\n- **Module**: cmd/cli\n- **Language**: Python\n- **Size**: L\n\n---\n\n## 9. CLI Toolkit Specification\n\n### Purpose","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775863601641,"end":1775863601659}}}}
